This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new activation function to improve the robustness of neural networks against adversarial attacks. It also involves training strategies and hyper-parameter tuning, which are common topics in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as adversarial attacks are a well-known problem in image classification tasks, and the paper's proposed method is evaluated on image datasets. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with improving the performance of AI models against adversarial attacks. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the security of machine learning models against adversarial attacks. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a new activation function for neural networks.
